context: Florida is served by <a0_0><b4_0>Amtrak<b4_0/>, operating numerous lines throughout, connecting the state's largest cities to points north in the United States and Canada<a0_0/>. The busiest Amtrak train stations in Florida in 2011 were: <b7_0><b8_0>Sanford<b8_0/><b7_0/> (259,944), Orlando (179,142), Tampa Union Station (140,785), Miami (94,556), and Jacksonville (74,733). Sanford, in Greater Orlando, is the southern terminus of the <a1_0>Auto Train, which originates at <b5_0>Lorton, Virginia<b5_0/>, south of Washington, D.C<a1_0/>.. Until 2005, Orlando was also the eastern terminus of the <a2_0><b6_0>Sunset Limited<b6_0/>, which travels across the southern United States via New Orleans, Houston, and San Antonio to its western terminus of Los Angeles<a2_0/>. Florida is served by two additional <a3_0>Amtrak trains (the Silver Star and the Silver Meteor), which operate between New York City and Miami<a3_0/>. Miami Central Station, the city's rapid transit, commuter rail, intercity rail, and bus hub, is under construction.
